INSERT INTO `ezcontentobject_attribute` VALUES(0, 187, 65, 0, 1045487555, '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>\n<section xmlns:image="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/image/" xmlns:xhtml="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/xhtml/" xmlns:custom="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/custom/"><paragraph>A class implementing <emphasize>Comparable</emphasize> interface must implement the <emphasize>compareTo() </emphasize>method.</paragraph><paragraph>e.g.</paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><literal>int i = this.compareTo(someOtherObject);\n</literal></paragraph><paragraph>&amp;nbsp;The compareTo() method returns an int with the following characteristics:</paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><ul><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">negative - if this object&amp;nbsp; &lt; someOtherObject</paragraph></li><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">zero - if this object&amp;nbsp; == someOtherObject</paragraph></li><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">positive - if this object &gt; someOtherObject</paragraph></li></ul></paragraph><paragraph>The <emphasize>sort() </emphasize>method uses compareTo to determine sort order of the List or object array.</paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><literal>class Person implements Comparable&lt;Person&gt;{ //Line 1\n     \n   private String lastName;\n   //...\n     \n   public int compareTo( Person p ){\n     return lastName.compareTo(p.getLastName()); //Line 2\n   }\n}</literal></paragraph><paragraph>In line 1 we declare that class <emphasize>Person </emphasize>implements <emphasize>Comparable </emphasize>in such a way that <emphasize>Person </emphasize>objects can be compared to other <emphasize>Person </emphasize>objects. In line 2 we implement <emphasize>compareTo() </emphasize>by comparing the two <emphasize>Person </emphasize>object''s last names. Since we know that the title are Strings, and that String implements Comparable, this is an easy way to sort our <emphasize>Person </emphasize>objects by last name.</paragraph></section>\n', 'ezxmltext', 266, 'eng-US', 2, 0, '', 4);
