ns of JavaScript APIs which developers can use to control browsers from the server. A server-side version of the TIBCO GI library is currently in alpha release, and the DWR project aims to expand this to cover other client side APIs including the Dojo Toolkit, JQuery, YUI, Ext and others. </line><line xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><strong>&amp;nbsp;</strong></line></paragraph><paragraph><strong>Adding DWR to Spring Project:</strong></paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><ol><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">Place dwr.jar in the WEB-INF/lib directory of your webapp. DWR also requires other jar files like commons-logging etc.</paragraph></li><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">Add the following to web.xml</paragraph></li></ol><literal>&lt;!-- Adding AJAX capability to J2EE app --&gt;\n&lt;servlet&gt;\n   &lt;servlet-name&gt;dwr&lt;/servlet&gt;\n   &lt;servlet-class&gt;org.directwebremoting.servlet.DwrServlet&lt;/servlet-class&gt;\n   &lt;init-param&gt;\n      &lt;param-name&gt;debug&lt;/param-name&gt;\n      &lt;param-value&gt;true&lt;/param-value&gt;\n   &lt;/init-param&gt;\n&lt;/servlet&gt;\n&lt;servlet-mapping&gt;\n   &lt;servlet-name&gt;dwr&lt;/servlet-name&gt;\n   &lt;url-pattern&gt;/dwr/*&lt;/url-pattern&gt;\n&lt;/servlet-mapping&gt;\n</literal></paragraph><paragraph>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 3. Create a file called dwr.xml that lives in WEB-INF alongside web.xml</paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><literal>&lt;!DOCTYPE dwr PUBLIC\n   "-//GetAhead Limited//DTD Direct Web Remoting 1.0//EN"\n   "http://www.getahead.ltd.uk/dwr/dwr10.dtd"&gt;\n\n&lt;dwr&gt;\n   &lt;allow&gt;\n      &lt;convert converter="bean" match="com.springinaction.pizza.domain.Customer"/&gt;\n      &lt;create creator="new" javascript="Customer"&gt;\n         &lt;param name="class"\n                      value="com.springinaction.pizza.service.CustomerServiceImpl" /&gt;\n      &lt;/create&gt;\n   &lt;/allow&gt;\n&lt;/dwr&gt;\n</literal></paragraph><paragraph><line xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">&amp;nbsp;The DWR config file defines what classes DWR can create and remote for use by Javascript. In the example above we are defining 2 classes that are remoted and giving the classes names in Javascript.</line><line xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">&amp;nbsp;The new creator that we used above uses the public no-args constructor that all JavaBeans must have. It is also worth remembering that DWR has a few restrictions:</line></paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><ul><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">Avoid reserved JavaScript words; Methods named after reserved words are automatically excluded. Most JavaScript reserved words are also Java reserved words, so you won''t be having a method called "try()" anyway. However the most common gotcha is "delete()", which has special meaning from JavaScript but not Java.</paragraph></li><li><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/">Overloaded methods can be involved in a bit of a lottery as to which gets called, so avoid overloaded methods.</paragraph></li></ul></paragraph><paragraph>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 4. Go to the following URL. <link url_id="11">http://localhost:8080/</link>_[YOUR-WEBAPP]_/dwr/</paragraph><paragraph>When you click on the class name "Customer". You''ll see the following. It shows how to get the Java class in JavaScript code.</paragraph><paragraph>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 5. You can use DWR in JavaScript code in the following way.</paragraph><paragraph xmlns:tmp="http://ez.no/namespaces/ezpublish3/temporary/"><literal>&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/sample/dwr/interface/Customer.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/sample/dwr/engine.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/sample/dwr/util.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;\n   function criteriaChanged(){\n      var phoneNumber = document.lookupForm.phoneNumber.value;\n      if(phoneNumber.length == 10){\n         var c = Customer.lookupCustomer(phoneNumber, updateResults);\n      }\n   }\n\n   function updateResults(str){\n      document.lookupForm.firstName,value=str.firstName;\n      document.lookupForm.lastName.value=str.lastName; \n   }\n\n&lt;/script&gt;\n\n&lt;form name="lookupForm"&gt;\n   &lt;input type="text" name="phoneNumber" onkeyup="criteriaChanged();"&gt;\n   First Name: &lt;input type="text" name="firstName"&gt;\n   Last Name: &lt;input type="text" name="lastName"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n</literal></paragraph></section>\n', 'ezxmltext', 518, 'eng-US', 2, 0, '', 7);
